ent to the following dry consistence classes in the ‘USDA Soil Survey Manual’ (Soil Survey Staff 1951):\r\n0\tLoose\r\n1\tSoft\r\n2\tSlightly hard\r\n3\tHard\r\n4\tVery hard\r\n5\tExtremely hard"}, "ErosionSeverityRill": {"@id": "ls:Erosion-severity-rill", "type": "string", "oneOf": [{"const": "ls:erosion-R-0", "description": "No rill erosion"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-R-1", "description": "Minor"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-R-2", "description": "Moderate"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-R-3", "description": "Severe"}], "title": "Rill erosion", "description": "A rill is a small channel up to 0.3 m deep, which can be largely obliterated by tillage operations (Houghton and Charman 1986)."}, "ErosionSeverityWave": {"@id": "ls:Erosion-severity-wave", "type": "string", "oneOf": [{"const": "ls:erosion-V-0", "description": "No wave erosion"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-V-1", "description": "Present"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-V-X", "description": "Not apparent"}], "title": "Wave erosion", "description": "Erosion of beaches, beach ridges and/or dunes. This is the removal of sand or soil from the margins of beaches, beach ridges, dunes, lakes or dams by wave action."}, "ErosionSeverityWind": {"@id": "ls:Erosion-severity-wind", "type": "string", "oneOf": [{"const": "ls:erosion-W-0", "description": "No wind erosion"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-W-1", "description": "Minor or present"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-W-2", "description": "Moderate"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-W-3", "description": "Severe"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-W-4", "description": "Very severe"}, {"const": "ls:erosion-W-X", "description": "Not apparent"}], "title": "Wind erosion", "description": "Give presence/absence or extent of accelerated erosion."}, "FieldTextureMineral": {"@id": "sp:Field-texture-mineral", "type": "string", "oneOf": [{"const": "sp:field-texture-CL", "description": "Clay loam"}, {"const": "sp:field-texture-CL-A", "description": "Sapric clay loam"}, {"const": "sp:field-texture-CL-I", "description": "Fibric clay loam"}, {"const"