o the smaller and further where necessary. For example, ''strong 50-100 mm columnar, parting to moderate 20-50 mm prismatic, parting to moderate\r\n10-20 mm angular blocky''. The word ''parting'' and not ''breaking'' is used. The term ''breaking'' is used when soil is fractured along planes other than natural planes of weakness.\r\n1\tLargest peds (in the type of soil observation described), parting to\r\n2\tNext size peds, parting to\r\n3\tNext size peds, ... and further, if required, to the primary ped."}, "GeomorphologyAgentInternal": {"@id": "lf:Geomorphology-agent-internal", "type": "string", "oneOf": [{"const": "lf:geomorphological-agent-DI", "description": "Diastrophism"}, {"const": "lf:geomorphological-agent-VO", "description": "Volcanism"}], "title": "Geomorphological agents - internal forces"}, "MicroreliefComponentBiotic": {"@id": "ls:Microrelief-component-biotic", "type": "string", "oneOf": [{"const": "ls:biotic-microrelief-component-D", "description": "Depression"}, {"const": "ls:biotic-microrelief-component-E", "description": "Elongate mound"}, {"const": "ls:biotic-microrelief-component-H", "description": "Hole"}, {"const": "ls:biotic-microrelief-component-L", "description": "Elongate depression"}, {"const": "ls:biotic-microrelief-component-M", "description": "Mound"}, {"const": "ls:biotic-microrelief-component-O", "description": "Other."}, {"const": "ls:biotic-microrelief-component-T", "description": "Terrace"}], "title": "Component of biotic relief", "description": "The component of the biotic relief."}, "TypeOfSubstrateObservation": {"@id": "subst:type-of-substrate-observation", "type": "string", "oneOf": [{"const": "subst:observation-type-A", "description": "Auger boring"}, {"const": "subst:observation-type-C", "description": "Relatively undisturbed soil core"}, {"const": "subst:observation-type-E", "description": "Existing vertical exposure"}, {"const": "subst:observation-type-P", "description": "Soil pit"}, {"const": "subst:observation-type-O", "